{
  "slug": "rate-limits-are-backpressure-with-a-policy",
  "title": "Rate limits are backpressure with a policy",
  "category": "tech",
  "kicker": "Traffic control",
  "hook": "A rate limit is not just saying no. It is telling traffic where the edge of fairness lives.",
  "readMinutes": 5,
  "date": "2026-06-18",
  "tags": [
    "rate-limits",
    "reliability"
  ],
  "beats": [
    {
      "num": "01 · the shape",
      "heading": "Unlimited is not a product plan",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">Without limits, one client can burn the shared pool for everyone. With crude limits, good clients get punished for normal spikes. The policy matters.</p>"
        },
        {
          "type": "terminal",
          "title": "api · throttled",
          "caption": "The useful signal is usually already there.",
          "lines": [
            {
              "t": "HTTP/1.1 429 Too Many Requests",
              "c": "err"
            },
            {
              "t": "Retry-After: 30",
              "c": ""
            },
            {
              "t": "X-RateLimit-Remaining: 0",
              "c": ""
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "graph",
          "center": "request",
          "nodes": [
            "client",
            "edge",
            "API",
            "queue",
            "db",
            "cache"
          ],
          "caption": "Systems stories get more interesting when you can feel the pressure move through the stack.",
          "action": "add load",
          "idle": "system steady",
          "running": "pressure moving downstream...",
          "done": "6 infrastructure layers reacted"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "num": "02 · the move",
      "heading": "Limit by the thing that consumes capacity",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">Sometimes that is user id, API key, tenant, IP, endpoint, cost unit, or write path. Match the limit to the resource you are protecting.</p>"
        },
        {
          "type": "code",
          "file": "limits.yml",
          "code": "checkout_write:\n  key: tenant_id\n  burst: 20\n  sustained_per_minute: 60\n  retry_after: true",
          "caption": "A good limit includes a recovery hint."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "num": "03 · the check",
      "heading": "Make rejection useful",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">Clients need status codes, retry headers, and docs. Operators need dashboards showing who is limited and why.</p>"
        },
        {
          "type": "lab",
          "title": "reliability control room",
          "caption": "Flip the switches and watch the story turn into a tiny operating model.",
